{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b43cb94f-8dd4-46d7-acd9-64583c7659ab","content":"The issue is clear. In F#, **file order in the `.fsproj` matters** — files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Domain.fs` is listed after `Services.fs`.\n\nFixing the compile order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_bMurx7pcdMdlreEAgD6bEr","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-1f87c052875f490c848524f05f2e1eeb/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-1f87c052875f490c848524f05f2e1eeb/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"848f4615-1583-4f8f-bcd6-1c17057717ab","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *before* them in the project file. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n```xml\n<Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n```\n\n`Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` is listed *after* `Services.fs`. The correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs` (defines types)\n2. `Services.fs` (uses Domain types)\n\n\n3. `Program.fs` (uses both)","outputTokens":460,"requestId":"7C20:9309E:AC6698:C50E07:6A0279AA"},"id":"3fb3f431-8056-4c54-8679-5c1455b8e309","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:52:02.112Z","parentId":"52ee8a30-4c6d-45b7-ac4b-fb9c02850a0e"}
